              "code": "-- Basic explain\nEXPLAIN SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = 'test@example.com';\n\n-- Explain with actual execution stats\nEXPLAIN ANALYZE SELECT * FROM orders WHERE order_date > '2023-01-01';\n\n-- Explain with buffers\nEXPLAIN (ANALYZE, BUFFERS) \nSELECT * FROM products WHERE price > 1000;\n\n-- Sample output interpretation:\n-- Seq Scan = Full table scan (may need index)\n-- Index Scan = Using index (good)\n-- Bitmap Heap Scan = Multiple index usage\n-- Nested Loop = Join method\n\n-- Common performance tips:\n-- 1. Use EXPLAIN ANALYZE to see actual performance\n-- 2. Look for sequential scans on large tables\n-- 3. Ensure statistics are up to date: ANALYZE table_name;\n-- 4. Check for missing indexes\n-- 5. Monitor slow queries in postgresql.conf"
